# ── Ancient kernel CVEs with no fix (disputed/won't-fix) ───────────────────
# These affect the Linux kernel shipped in the Debian base image (linux-libc-dev)
# and are NOT exploitable in a Docker container context (no kernel access).

# Memory exhaustion via crafted Graphics Execution Manager (GEM) objects —
# requires local access and specific GPU hardware. Disputed since 2013.
CVE-2013-7445

# f2fs filesystem crafted image — requires mounting attacker-controlled
# filesystems, not applicable in containerized web server.
CVE-2019-19449

# f2fs out-of-bounds write — same as above, requires filesystem mount.
CVE-2019-19814

# Privilege escalation via user namespaces — requires local unprivileged
# access to the host kernel, not applicable inside containers.
CVE-2021-3847

# Descendant dumpable SUID bypass — host kernel issue, not container.
CVE-2021-3864
